<TITLE> Shahidul Islam gets bail in wealth case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 23 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court granted bail to former BNP MP Shahidul Islam on Monday in an illegal wealth case. The bail will be in force till the investigation report in the case is presented in court, said Dhaka senior special judge AMM Bashirullah. Shahid surrendered to the court Sunday. His wife, co-accused in the same case, has also secured bail. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case on April 6, 2008, accusing the former MP from Kushtia-2 and his wife of illegally amassing wealth of Tk 1.31 crore beyond known sources of income and concealing information about assets worth Tk 56.49 lakh. bdnew
